<span class="displaytext"><b><em>straight talk takes a detour as sen. (candidate last) now claims to be optimistic</em></b> <p><b> <em>"(candidate last) talked about reviving the auto industry, but (candidate last) said some michigan industries cannot be resurrected. 'i've got to give you some straight talk: some of the jobs that have left the state of michigan are not coming back,' he said. 'they are not. and i am sorry to tell you that.'"</em> </b> (michael levenson, "staking out the next battlegrounds," <em>the boston globe</em>, 1/10/08) </p><p><b> <u>why is sen. (candidate last) changing his tune in michigan? <br/></u> </b> <br/> <b>just days ago, sen. (candidate full) said he was merely "aware" of michigan's woes, and insisted that jobs that left michigan "are not coming back."</b> "'i'm aware of the economic difficulties here in the state of michigan,' (candidate last) said (candidate last) talked about reviving the auto industry, but (candidate last) said some michigan industries cannot be resurrected. 'i've got to give you some straight talk: some of the jobs that have left the state of michigan are not coming back,' he said. 'they are not. and i am sorry to tell you that.'" (michael levenson, "staking out the next battlegrounds," <em>the boston globe</em>, 1/10/08) </p><p><b>in the meantime, gov. (candidate last) has vowed to fight for michigan jobs, and remains optimistic.</b> "'they have watched michigan go through a one-state recession for, what, a decade?' he said. 'they talk about it, they say they're aware of it, they say there are some jobs that just aren't coming back. but what have they done to help michigan?' ... (candidate last) said michigan should remain optimistic. 'michigan has everything that it takes to remain an economic powerhouse, as long as it has a partner in washington,' he said. 'i will be that partner.'" (michael levenson, "staking out the next battlegrounds," <em>the boston globe</em>, 1/10/08) </p><p><b>so now today, sen. (candidate full) claimed, "we can restore detroit's supremacy... i'm optimistic."</b> "'we can restore detroit's supremacy in the automotive world,' (candidate last) said at the andiamo celebrity showroom. 'i'm optimistic.'" (charlie cain, "(candidate last) campaigns on promise of strong national defense," <em>the detroit news</em>, 1/12/08)</p></span>



